verses.text:
Have not I commanded thee? Be strong and of a good courage;
be not afraid, neither be thou dismayed: for the \nd LORD\nd* thy
God \add is\add* with thee whithersoever thou goest.

And it came to pass, when the people removed from their tents,
to pass over Jordan, and the priests bearing the ark of the covenant
before the people;

And he commanded them, saying, Behold, ye shall lie in wait
against the city, \add even\add* behind the city: go not very far
from the city, but be ye all ready:

They did work wilily, and went and made as if they had been
ambassadors, and took old sacks upon their asses, and wine bottles,
old, and rent, and bound up;

Now it came to pass, when Adoni-zedek king of Jerusalem had
heard how Joshua had taken Ai, and had utterly destroyed it; as he had
done to Jericho and her king, so he had done to Ai and her king;
and how the inhabitants of Gibeon had made peace with Israel, and were
among them;

So Joshua took all that land, the hills, and all the south
country, and all the land of Goshen, and the valley, and the plain,
and the mountain of Israel, and the valley of the same;

And these \add are\add* the kings of the country which Joshua
and the children of Israel smote on this side Jordan on the west,
from Baal-gad in the valley of Lebanon even unto the mount Halak,
that goeth up to Seir; which Joshua gave unto the tribes of Israel
\add for\add* a possession according to their divisions;

With whom the Reubenites and the Gadites have received their
inheritance, which Moses gave them, beyond Jordan eastward, \add even\add*
as Moses the servant of the \nd LORD\nd* gave them;

From Aroer, that \add is\add* upon the bank of the river Arnon,
and the city that \add is\add* in the midst of the river, and all the
plain of Medeba unto Dibon;

And their coast was from Aroer, that \add is\add* on the bank
of the river Arnon, and the city that \add is\add* in the midst of the
river, and all the plain by Medeba;

Heshbon, and all her cities that \add are\add* in the plain;
Dibon, and Bamoth-baal, and Beth-baal-meon,\f + \fr 13.17  \ft Bamoth-baal…: or, the high places of Baal, and house of
Baal-meon\f*

And their coast was Jazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and
half the land of the children of Ammon, unto Aroer that \add is\add*
before Rabbah;

And the name of Hebron before \add was\add* Kirjath-arba;
\add which Arba was\add* a great man among the Anakims. And the land
had rest from war.

And the border of the children of Ephraim according to their
families was \add thus:\add* even the border of their inheritance
on the east side was Ataroth-addar, unto Beth-horon the upper;

And the border went out toward the sea to Michmethah on the north
side; and the border went about eastward unto Taanath-shiloh, and
passed by it on the east to Janohah;

The border went out from Tappuah westward unto the river Kanah;
and the goings out thereof were at the sea. This \add is\add* the
inheritance of the tribe of the children of Ephraim by their families.

And their border went up toward the sea, and Maralah, and
reached to Dabbasheth, and reached to the river that \add is\add*
before Jokneam;

And the coast reacheth to Tabor, and Shahazimah, and Beth-shemesh;
and the outgoings of their border were at Jordan: sixteen cities
with their villages.

Then came near the heads of the fathers of the Levites unto
Eleazar the priest, and unto Joshua the son of Nun, and unto the
heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel;

Thus they gave to the children of Aaron the priest Hebron
with her suburbs, \add to be\add* a city of refuge for the slayer;
and Libnah with her suburbs,

Be ye therefore very courageous  to keep and to do all that is
written in the book of the law of Moses, that ye turn not aside therefrom
\add to\add* the right hand or \add to\add* the left;
